scheduler

Class ProcessScheduler

  • java.lang.Object
    • scheduler.ProcessScheduler
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    RandomScheduler, RoundRobinScheduler, WeightedScheduler

    public abstract class ProcessScheduler
extends java.lang.Object
    ProcessScheduler class is an abstract class which manages the processes by a given scheduler type. It has an array of processes, where the index represents the PID of the process; an array of inputs and an array of outputs; the current index of current input and the number of processes.
    Author:
    razvan

    • Field Detail

      • process

        private Process[] process
        An array of running processes. The index represents the PID of the process.

      • inputs

        private int[] inputs
        An array of inputs. Every input is processed by a process chosen by the Scheduler

      • outputs

        private OutputClass[] outputs
        An array of outputs. Is is used to store the output and details about process which computed the value, and for printing these data to file.

      • numProcesses

      • cache

        The cache memory. It is used to store some values computed before, to increase performance.

    • Constructor Detail

      • ProcessScheduler

        public ProcessScheduler(int numProcesses,
                        java.lang.String cacheType,
                        int cacheSize)
        Initialize the number of processes, the cache type and its size. Also it initializes the cache. This constructor may be used when the user wants to implement its own process scheduler.
        Parameters:
        numProcesses - number of processes
        cacheType - the type of cache
        cacheSize - the size of cache

      • runProcessAtID

        protected void runProcessAtID(int id)
        Run a process by its ID. This method will check if caching mechanism is running, if yes the process will be searched in cache, otherwise it will be run. Also after running/getting the value form cache, the output will be set.
        Parameters:
        id - the PID of process

      • runScheduler

        public void runScheduler()
        This method runs the scheduler. It checks for some errors and then it runs processes, governed by an implemented scheduler, for each input.

      • generatePID
